name: Yaser Jabbar
summary: A major investigation is underway at Great Ormond Street Hospital, following concerns over the operations performed by a former surgeon. Over 700 children have been identified as having been treated by the surgeon, with allegations of botched procedures and inappropriate and unnecessary surgeries. The investigation has revealed serious injuries and lifelong damage resulting from these operations, leaving children in severe pain and with deformities. Despite these findings, it has been reported that the surgeon is still operating on children in Dubai. Families of the affected children are being represented by a law firm, and the hospital has issued a statement acknowledging their concerns and promising a thorough review.

name: Mika Stojsavljevic
summary: British 15-year-old Mika Stojsavljevic has achieved a remarkable feat by becoming the first British player in 15 years to win the US Open junior title. Stojsavljevic's victory marks a significant milestone in British tennis, following in the footsteps of Heather Watson, who won the same title in 2009. Stojsavljevic's success on the court has drawn comparisons to Andy Murray, who won the boys' singles title at Flushing Meadows in 2005. The young tennis prodigy's journey to the final included a victory over Iva Jovic in the semi-finals.

The Independent notes that Carsley is from Northern Ireland, which has a complex political and national identity, and BBC.com explains the historical context of the British national anthem. The Telegraph reports that Carsley has previously stated his intention not to sing the anthem. Football365 characterizes the reaction to Carsley's silence as "embarrassing," while Metro.co.uk provides biographical information about the manager. The Sun highlights the division among England fans over Carsley's decision, and GB News expresses outrage, arguing that the anthem is unifying. The Guardian reports that Carsley has put his mixed feelings about the anthem behind him.

This revelation has sparked a flurry of media attention, with headlines highlighting his "greatest social experiment" and the surprise and disbelief expressed by his followers.
